Text.SourceString: I’m starting to worry about the recycling center near the park.//Should I stop piling up my recyclables there?
I don’t know if you notice, but it’s looking like it’s overflowing.
I’m starting to worry about the recycling center near the park.//Should I stop piling up my recyclables there?
I don’t know if you notice, but it’s looking like it’s overflowing.
Certainly… There are empty sites here that we can repurpose.

Mr. Mayor thought that a community garden would make a great outdoor activity.//As their doctor, I agree that it would be a great idea.//<portrait=happy>It will give people more reason to move their bodies.
Certainly… There are empty sites here that we can repurpose.

Mr. Mayor thought that a community garden would make a great outdoor activity.//As their doctor, I agree that it would be a great idea.//<portrait=happy>It will give people more reason to move their bodies.
Certainly… There are empty sites here that we can repurpose.

Mr. Mayor thought that a community garden would make a great outdoor activity.//As their doctor, I agree that it would be a great idea.//<portrait=happy>It will give people more reason to move their bodies.
I can see that building facilities like a recycling center or a community garden can be good for us.//<portrait=annoyed>But I don’t know about upgrading other buildings.
I like how some of the buildings here are old. Like the mansion and lighthouse...//They feel like a time capsule, you know?
I can see that building facilities like a recycling center or a community garden can be good for us.//<portrait=annoyed>But I don’t know about upgrading other buildings.
I like how some of the buildings here are old. Like the mansion and lighthouse...//They feel like a time capsule, you know?

Not really, I’m averaging at around four hours-ish a day…//I usually work from 10 to 2, taking patients, reviewing medical histories, or doing inventory.//Charles runs the cash register most of the time.
Hmm… If I had to choose…//My most favorite part of the job is creating health care plans for my patients.
I’m used to being in high-stress situations.//I feel like that’s when my knowledge and training really kick in.
It sounds horrible, but the adrenaline rush is addictive.
Paying attention to what you eat is a great way to stay healthy in the long run.//Prevention is worth more than any cure.
Make sure to include fresh vegetables in your diet.//They are a great source of fiber and nutrients.
It would also make my job a whole lot easier! Heh heh
Yup, I get all my groceries at Sam's.//I love how he uses local resources.
Sam’s only bad thing is that you can’t really find off-season items.
Just holler at me whenever you have questions about medicine or health.//I know people get nervous about little things, like moles or rash sometimes.
Let me help by giving you peace of mind.
Yeah, that’s alright. Being in the sun is fine, as long as you remember to wear sunscreen.
Oh, another thing!//<portrait=normal>Remember to reapply sunscreen every so often. That part is important and often forgotten.
Playing pool after work is a great way to make new friends.//<portrait=normal>But to be frank, I do it mostly because I think I’m pretty good at it.//<portrait=happy>It feels good to win, heh heh.
None taken, it’s true. I should wear regular clothes more.//<portrait=normal>I’m too lazy to change clothes after my shift, so I just go around in my scrub.
I notice that the people here love fishing.//I’m all for it because I think it’s important to unwind.
Yeah! Fishing totally trains patience.
Well, for me, anyway.//<portrait=normal>Playing chess is all about planning and strategy, just like with health.
Heh heh... You got me!//<portrait=normal>I do always find a way to bring the conversation back to health talk.
I don’t usually work on Fridays unless I have an appointment in advance.//Or if there is an emergency or something.
I’m not too worried about it. The clinic is very quiet in general.//<NpcName>Charles</> alone will do just fine.
How has your week been so far?
I think I might need to go to Sam tomorrow.
We sell medicines and vitamins at the clinic.//You may want to have them in your backpack, because they can immediately restore your health.
Useful for an active person like you, no?
Yup, I get all my groceries at Sam's.//I love how he uses local resources.
Sam’s only bad thing is that you can’t really find off-season items.
I’m not a very good cook, but I try to eat home-made meals when I can.//They’re better for you.
I still eat out quite a bit, though! Heh heh... Old habits die hard, huh?

My tattoos?//<portrait=normal>Most of them are from all the places that I was dispatched to. The experience that I got joining the universal doctor program stayed with me forever.//It’s part of me, just like these tattoos.
Ready for Monday, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Make sure to drink enough water, okay.//Our body needs it.
It’s so easy to get carried away and forget listening to our bodies.//I’m guilty of that too.
Ugh… So true! Fashion is hard.
I tried "fashion," or whatever, back in med-school,//and let’s just say that I’m glad the community was not big on social media back then.
I don’t need any reminder of my med-school days.//Though, I do have some old pictures in a box somewhere.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I will show you someday.
Who knows...

One of the things that I find most challenging about being a doctor is that sometimes patients lie.//<portrait=normal>While they are harmless and don’t affect anything in most cases, it’s always best, to be honest with your doctor.
It’s important for doctors to know your complete medical history to give you the best care possible.
That’s an idea. Yeah, I should probably wear my coat like <NpcName>Charles</>.//<portrait=normal>He looks sleek in that coat, doesn’t he?
But it’s just so hot and restricting.//Can’t run in peace too, ‘cause that coat is flapping when you run in it.
I’m so used to being in scrubs, it feels weird to wear anything else. Other clothing feels restricting, you know.
I DO like green!//<portrait=happy>Can you really tell?! Hah!
You’re simple too, huh? I’m the same way.//As long as there is warm food on the table, it counts as a good day.
I’m not good at volleyball yet, but I won’t say no if someone dares me to play.
I spent my youth working for universal doctor programs around the world.//It’s a program in which medical professionals are sent away to foreign places to provide medical assistants.
The pay wasn’t good, but you get one heck of experience on top of helping those in need.
Besides, being in foreign land opens your mind, and you get to build a crazy thick skin.

One of the things that I find most challenging about being a doctor is that sometimes patients lie.//<portrait=normal>While they are harmless and don’t affect anything in most cases, it’s always best, to be honest with your doctor.
It’s important for doctors to know your complete medical history to give you the best care possible.
As a farmer, you must get a lot of daily exercises, ya?
A pet? Hmm… <NpcName>Millie</> has a lizard that only comes out of its hiding when she’s home.//<portrait=annoyed>Does that count?
I’m not sure if it’s male or female. All I know is that she calls the lizard "<NpcName>Tin</>."
I spent my youth working for universal doctor programs around the world.//It’s a program in which medical professionals are sent away to foreign places to provide medical assistants.
The pay wasn’t good, but you get one heck of experience on top of helping those in need.
Besides, being in foreign land opens your mind, and you get to build a crazy thick skin.
Ugh… So true! Fashion is hard.
I tried "fashion," or whatever, back in med-school,//and let’s just say that I’m glad the community was not big on social media back then.
I’m trying my best to lead a healthy life, but some days are harder than the others.
The plan is to spend the day relaxing and taking things slow. What about you?
Can’t just wear anything on my workday, though. I need to wear clothing that lets me move quickly in case of an emergency.
No, I’m not too picky. As long as they’re comfy, I’m game.
Do you like to hang out at Local Tavern, <PlayerName>$player</>? I usually go there on the weekend for their live music.
That <NpcName>Theo</> is really something, isn't he?
Easier said than done, for sure. It’s not easy for me to find someone that I want to spend my life with.
It’s true that I never really thought about settling down and have a family because I was busy, but truth be told, long-term commitments scare me.
I don’t have work tomorrow. Why?
If you need anything, <NpcName>Charles</> should be in.
Maybe tomorrow is the day that I finally go grocery shopping… Who knows, right?
Don’t count on it, though.
Easier said than done, for sure. It’s not easy for me to find someone that I want to spend my life with.
It’s true that I never really thought about settling down and have a family because I was busy, but truth be told, long-term commitments scare me.
Well, yeah, but not all of them. Not all of my tattoos have meaning behind them…
Not everything has to have a deep meaning behind them. Sometimes you just have to go with your guts.
My hair has been green for so long. If you asked me what my real hair color is, I would not know how to answer.
You've seen me where?!
I don’t want to spook you, but I don’t think that was me. I don’t go to the forest.
Easier said than done, for sure. It’s not easy for me to find someone that I want to spend my life with.
It’s true that I never really thought about settling down and have a family because I was busy, but truth be told, long-term commitments scare me.
You've seen me where?!
I don’t want to spook you, but I don’t think that was me. I don’t go to the forest.
Here is a non-medical tip for you, eat your food in one sitting, so it doesn’t go stale.
That is funny, isn’t it? The food here doesn’t seem to rot.
I think I got a bit too much sun yesterday at the beach.
I don’t know what it is about me, but no matter what time I fall asleep, I always wake up at 6am.
Oh! You too?! What a fun coincidence.
Don't overwork yourself, <PlayerName>$player</>. I don't wanna see you in the clinic.
I do like to see you around, though. Maybe I can dare you a game of pool sometimes? You look like a good pool player.
I guess I never really know if I’m actually an animal person or not. Because I have never had a pet my entire life.
I feel like I’m missing out on something here.
When I actually get a pet, I really want to name them Pat.
Oh, no reason. I just like the name Pat.
I love how pet owners are so passionate about what kind of person they are. I want to join the crowd and say things like "I’m a cat person," or "I’m a lizard person."
The whole shebang is just fascinating!
<PlayerName>$player</>! What a pleasant surprise!
I love how pet owners are so passionate about what kind of person they are. I want to join the crowd and say things like "I’m a cat person," or "I’m a lizard person."
The whole shebang is just fascinating!
Thank you for being so supportive of me. I’m so glad to have someone like you in my life.
I’ve met a lot of people in life, and you’re different, <PlayerName>$player</>...
Yeah, and you know what’s interesting? Wanting to help people and actually do the job are two completely different things.
The crazy thing about living near the river is the on-going fear of a flood when it rains a little.
The good news is that <NpcName>Millie</>'s house doesn’t have a rat problem. I’m not sure if that’s related, but I suppose no-rat counts as a win.
Don't overwork yourself, <PlayerName>$player</>. I don't wanna see you in the clinic.
I do like to see you around though, maybe I can dare you a game of pool sometimes? You look like a good pool $player.
I don’t know what it is about me, but no matter what time I fall asleep, I always wake up at 6am.
Oh! You too?! What a fun coincidence.
Thank you for being so supportive of me. I’m so glad to have someone like you in my life.
I’ve met a lot of people in life, and you’re special, <PlayerName>$player</>...
Want to play pool with me? I can use some win. Heh heh...
<NpcName>Luke</> is old news... We’re meant to be just friends. Nothing more can come out of it. We don't dance the same way, if you catch my drift.
I’m preoccupied with... Umm... Someone new now. Besides, I think there is something about people who work with their hands that are just so... Admirable.
I don’t know what it is about me, but no matter what time I fall asleep, I always wake up at 6am.
Oh! You too?! What a fun coincidence.
The crazy thing about living near the river, is the on-going fear about a flood when it rains a little.
The good news is that <NpcName>Millie</>'s house doesn’t have a rat problem. I’m not sure if that’s related, but I suppose no-rat counts as a win.
Hmm… Is that a new shirt?
That looks good. Works well with your... Err... Hair. Makes you look sharp.

I just need a house, with its own kitchen and a place to read my journals, then I’m good. I will then retire, and work only 2 days out of the week. I plan to spend the rest of my week publishing medical articles.
Until I save enough money to afford that, I’m going to keep working 4 days a week.
Have you ate, <PlayerName>$player</>? Please make sure that you eat on time, okay. Something healthy to boost your immune, maybe.
I worry about you...
It wasn’t easy for me to find someone that I wanted to spend my whole life with.
A relationship seemed like a long commitment at first, but when you know, you know, right?
You look spiffy today, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Oh my! I meant you look nice... Nice nice nice. You don’t look bad or anything.
I should start staying at the house more. It feels like such a waste to pay all that rent, but I’m never home.
Yup! Got that right. <NpcName>Millie</> is never home either. So it gets boring, really fast at the house. Unless you… Umm… Want to visit me sometimes. We can have the house for ourselves.
Durian has a strong scent. I know some people love them because of that, like <NpcName>Noah</>. If someone gives me a durian, will it eat it? Yes.
… But am I ever going to go out of my way to find one? No.
I heard that you like tacos. Is that right?
Hmm… I overheard it from <NpcName>Sunny</>. Anyway, we should totally check out <NpcName>Emma</>'s Taco Truck sometimes.
I personally love curry, both red and green.
No, I don’t mind other food either. I’m not very picky in that department. But I have to say though, some fruits have a very strong scent, like durian.
You’re so fun to talk to. One of the coolest people I’ve met, for sure.
You can always depend on me, you know that, right? If you ever need anything. Just name it.
I heard that you like tacos. Is that right?
Hmm… I overheard it from <NpcName>Sunny</>. Anyway, we should totally check out <NpcName>Emma</>'s Taco Truck sometimes.
You look spiffy today, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Oh my! I meant you look nice... Nice nice nice. You don’t look bad or anything.
Durian has a strong scent. I know some people love them because of that, like <NpcName>Noah</>. If someone gives me a durian, will it eat it? Yes.
But am I ever going to go out of my way to find one? No.
There is an empty room in <NpcName>Jack</>'s ranch, complete with its compact kitchen and a place to relax.
I was going to rent it, but I thought <NpcName>Millie</>'s place was closer to work. Besides, she charges a lot less than <NpcName>Jack</> does.
Hah hah! No, we don't do home visits often. Well, <NpcName>Charles</> does, actually. I only do it for an emergency.
For you, <PlayerName>$player</>… If you think you might need extra care... Something for me to... Err... Look at. I can stop by the cabin and make an exception for you.
I was walking home last night and almost fell into the river. This town can use extra lamp posts.
After all these years of moving around, I have never felt so accepted than when I’m here.
Not in my dictionary. I’m not going to give up. One day I’m going to make the best curry on the island and be the curry master.
<NpcName>Frank</> currently holds the title… He is a great cook, isn’t he?! Hmmph. Hard to beat.
In a way, we are kind of alike, <PlayerName>$player</>. I came here looking for some peace of mind and a place to fit in.
I’m glad that I did.
It feels so weird calling myself a doctor because I don’t feel like one deep down.
In my head, I have this idea of doctors being very serious people. Whatever that means.
I feel so close to you... I can smell you from here.
It's nice... You smell really nice.
In a way, we are kind of alike, <PlayerName>$player</>. I came here looking for some peace of mind and a place to fit in.
I’m glad that I did.
I spent years fitting into cycles of new groups of people. It’s nice to keep the same bunch long enough to celebrate my birthday with.
There is an empty room in <NpcName>Jack</>'s ranch, complete with its compact kitchen and a place to relax.
I was going to rent it, but I thought <NpcName>Millie</>'s place was closer to work. Besides, she charges a lot less than <NpcName>Jack</> does.
I used to think that I need to be on constant vigilance to feel excitement out of life. But nope. Things are really exciting with you around.
It's nice to find someone with the same sense of humor.
Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>? As in <PlayerName>$player</> <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>It’s nice to finally meet you! I'm <NpcName>Yuri</>.
I'm one of the doctors here.//So, if you need any medical advice or a friend. Feel free to find me!
Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>? As in <PlayerName>$player</> <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>It’s nice to finally meet you! My name is <NpcName>Yuri</> too. Isn't that neat?

Special.SourceString: introduction, if Player is named Scott

Text.SourceString: I'm one of the doctors here.//So, if you need any medical advice or a friend. Feel free to find me!
Yeah, I heard about Pufferfish Corp. moving in...//<portrait=annoyed>It’s too bad, huh?
The islanders aren’t too happy about it either.
The other day, I was at the store looking for some curly kale for my mid-day snack, but Sam didn’t have any.
Perhaps it isn’t kale season anymore.
You can get tulip, wasabi and celery this time of year.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmmm... What else.
Hang on... Not celery! I don’t think it’s celery season yet. Is that right?
Do you like to hang out at the tavern, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I usually go there on the weekend for their live music.
Spring literally just arrived and it feels like <NpcName>Charles</> has spent hours sneezing his nose out.//I must admit, it gets me concerned.
I took a walk near the lake the other day and saw so many colorful flowers.//What a season?!
Sure am! I’m trying my best to lead a healthy life, but some days are harder than the others.
There are so many coconuts at the beach, this time of year.
Wow... I had so much fun on Disco Day! <NpcName>Charles</> looked so festive with all those colors on him. Heh heh heh...//Did you see it?!
We’re cleaning up the beach soon.
Good thing the beach clean up starts at 11.//It gives me a bit of time in the morning to stop by the clinic and pick up some stuff.
If you like mushrooms, black trumpets and matsutakes are currently sprouting in the woodland.
I got the information from <NpcName>Dinda</>.//She goes to the woodland often and has an eye for scavenging.
<NpcName>Millie</> has a lizard that only comes out from his hiding when she is home.//<portrait=happy>Cute little thing.
She names the lizard <NpcName>Tin</>. What a fun name...
<NpcName>Millie</> has a lizard that only comes out from his hiding when she is home.//<portrait=happy>Cute little thing.
She names the lizard <NpcName>Tin</>. What a fun name...
It’s relaxing to read at the cemetary.//It’s the last place that people expect me to be at and I get a minimal distraction.
I slept at 3 last night, and now I’m absolutely drained.//<portrait=concerned>Hmmph. I need to stop doing that to myself.
I had things in my mind. Hard to shake off sometimes.
Yeah, I notice that too. With the weather getting colder, I see fewer and fewer people outside.
Oh gosh, yes! Piping hot curry would be perfect right now.
I’m not going to tell you how to live your life, but please wash your hands often. We touch so many things throughout the day, who knows what kind of things are on our hands.
I thought I would have more time to read this winter, but I’m more swamped than ever right now.
I slept at 3 last night, and now I’m absolutely drained.
I had things in my mind. Hard to shake off sometimes.
Oh gosh, yes! Piping hot curry would be perfect right now.
The rain doesn’t change anything, I think...//<portrait=annoyed>But it does slow life down a little bit.
But it must be convenient for farmers like yourself…//<portrait=annoyed>A bit? You don’t have to water your plants today, do you?
I wish I could sleep in today. It just seems like the perfect weather to wake up late and sleep early.
No, no tavern today. I have a lot of chores to do.
I wish I could sleep in today. It just seems like the perfect weather to wake up late and sleep early.
No, no tavern today. I have a lot of chores to do.
The rain doesn’t change anything, I think...//<portrait=annoyed>But it does slow life down a little bit.
But it must be convenient for farmers like yourself…//<portrait=annoyed>A bit? You don’t have to water your plants today, do you?
I’m trying to get more people to go out and garden.//It’s a simple way to get a daily excercise.
Oh gosh, yes! Piping hot curry would be perfect right now.
Oh gosh, yes! Piping hot curry would be perfect right now.
Is it snowing again outside or something?!
You would think that it would have stopped by now.
I can use one of those thick knitted blankets right now. Hmmph...
I learned a lot from <NpcName>Ling</>. She is very knowledgeable about coral reefs and this island.
I think she’s been living here for a long time, but I’m not exactly sure how long.
Aww… You too?!//<portrait=normal>I love coming here after work and just read some medical journals until sunset.
Four. I’m subscribed to four journals, and I have published a handful of them myself.//They’re mostly about the interesting cases that I’ve encountered while I was abroad.
Sometimes quiet is exactly what we need, isn’t it?
A little health tip, bring vitamins with you when you're chopping woods in the forest or out hunting.//It can boost your health quickly, so you can avoid an emergency trip to the clinic.
Right, but still. Even though we’re closed on Sundays, <NpcName>Charles</> and I are always on call in case of an emergency. So, don’t worry, okay!
I like my scrubs. They’re comfortable and easy to clean.//But I should probably wear my white coat on occasion…//<portrait=happy>Change things up a bit.
You know, like <NpcName>Charles</>. He looks neat in his coat.
<NpcName>Charles</> is one of the most knowledgeable medical doctors that I’ve ever met.//You are in good hands here.
Oh my! Another fake medical report with a "unicorn finger problem for Yoorie."//This is his doing, trying to elevate the boredom.
<NpcName>Charles</>!! It’s not funny. I AM BUSY.//<portrait=happy>Okay… It’s a bit funny.
How <NpcName>Charles</> finds time for pranks is beyond me.
<NpcName>Betty</> is one of my easy patients. I really like working with her.
Oh, trust me. There are plenty of folks here that are on my hard-patients list. My lips are sealed, though.
I hardly have the time to travel anymore, but I don’t regret it. And to be perfectly frank, I kind of like not moving around every other season.
Who knew boring can be so much fun.
I just submitted my billing for the week. That felt good.
Doing paperwork isn’t a lot of fun, but it’s necessary.
In a way, we are kind of alike, <PlayerName>$player</>. I came here looking for some peace of mind and a place to fit in.
I’m glad that I did.
Free books excite me. Is that sad?
They’re free for us. <NpcName>Charles</> and I are free to subscribe to as many medical journals as we want. The town will cover the fees.
It’s very generous of them.
I’m here to pick up new readings. I have run out of materials already.
Umm... No. I can’t smell anything. Though I’ve lived in an abandoned school, right next to a dumpster once, for two years.
So that may have ruined my nose a little… The rent was free.
Whenever I can, basically. Dancing is an instant mood booster.//<portrait=happy>Hey, we should go dancing together sometimes.
I can’t dance well, but as long as I don’t hurt anyone and it makes me feel good, who really cares?
You’re simple too, huh? I’m the same way.//As long as there is warm food on the table, it counts as a good day.//<portrait=annoyed>… In a bit.
I may have one too many punches. I’m going to stop and call it a night.
I felt like I should settle somewhere and develop meaningful relationships after years of jumping from one place to another.
Sometimes I envy <NpcName>Dinda</> and <NpcName>Joko</>. They seem to have such a full life.
Yeah… That’s true. My life is full. But I think I don’t mind a spouse for lonely days like these, you know.
I can’t believe I just said that to you. Now I’m embarrassed.
I was going to practice some volleyball earlier, but there was nobody outside.//So, I decided to chill here instead.
Wah… I’m craving seafood today.//Let’s see what Jim is cooking up.
Phew! The sun is a bit strong out, isn’t it?//I think I will enjoy the beach from inside here.
Nice to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=happy>Are you buying or selling?
The radishes here are incredibly crunchy to pickle.
The radishes here are incredibly crunchy to pickle.
The eggplants here are incredibly crunchy to pickle.
The eggplants here are incredibly crunchy to pickle.
I don’t really go to the forest.//I suppose, to me where I live, Garden Lane is foresty enough.
Besides, what am I going to do there anyway?//It’s not like I can just start mining.
I should go to Sam's and pick up a few things. There was basically nothing in the fridge this morning.
An apple. What did you have for breakfast? I thought we had nothing at home until I found a couple of apples from who knows when. Oh well… Tasted fine.
I should go to Sam's and pick up a few things. There was basically nothing in the fridge this morning.
An apple. What did you have for breakfast? I thought we had nothing at home until I found a couple of apples from who knows when. Oh well… Tasted fine.
A1-1. Who used to run the clinic before you and Charles took over?

A1-1a. Charles was here first years before I moved in. He worked with <NPCName>Dr. Murphey</> and <NPCName>Dr. Chen</> for a bit. Those 2 were the OG. She...<NPCName>Dr. Chen</>, was a surgeon, I believe. They’re both retired now. There is a picture of them somewhere in the clinic. [image icon of the picture]
B1-1. How many tattoos do you have?
B1-1a. Not a lot. Some of my tattoos kind of mix with one another. What about you, <PlayerName>$player</>? Do you have any tattoos?
Oh! Very cool! You have to show me your tattoos sometimes. What is it of?
Ah, you’re one of those. Hah hah! One of those ‘my tattoos have deep meanings’ folks. Not that its a bad thing. Deep thinker...I’d like to call it.

Special.SourceString: B2-2. No, but maybe in the future. I've been wanting to get one... Just haven't found the design that I <Italic>like like</>... You know what I mean?

Text.SourceString: Hah! Cheeky. Yeah, I think you have a massive back tattoo of a purple dinosaur doing ballet.
C1-1. What’s with hating flowers?

C1-1a. Aahh… I don’t know. It just seems like a waste...you know? I can’t eat it. They’re useless to me. Besides, <NPCName>Charles</> is mad allergic. He wouldn’t stop sneezing if I bring them to the clinic. And I’m never home...so I can’t appreciate it at home...I can’t appreciate it at the clinic. I can’t eat it… I said that twice, didn’t I? Anyway, yeah!
D1-1. The museum opening was a doozy. It was only me who showed up...and <NPCName>Scott</>.
D1-1a. Oh that! Yeah, I heard from <NPCName>Millie</>. <NPCName>Scott</> was pretty bumped that only one person showed up.
D2-1a. I was preoccupied with...work. And honestly, the museum isn’t really my thing. Glad you made it, though. I’ll show up the next time.
D2-2a. Yeah. She’s running the museum and library. I’m glad that the museum is finally open. She’s so excited about it filling up with artifacts soon...all she’s talking about at home.

Special.SourceString: D2-2. So, Millie is like...Scott’s boss or something?
